Metropolitan Museum of Art API Project
This project leverages the Metropolitan Museum of Art Collection API to enable users to search for and explore artworks from the museum's vast collection, which includes over 470,000 works of art spanning 19 departments.

Features
Metropolitan Museum of Art API
Department Search: Allows users to search and select from various departments such as "Ancient Near Eastern Art" or "Egyptian Art".
Artwork Search: Enables users to search for artworks by title or keyword within a selected department.
Display Results: Displays the first 10 search results, showcasing the artwork's title.
API Endpoints
The application interacts with the following Metropolitan Museum of Art Collection API endpoints:

1. List Departments
Endpoint: GET https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/departments
Provides a list of all departments in the museum's collection.
2. Search for Artworks
Endpoint: GET https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/search?q={searchTerm}
Allows searching for artworks by title or keyword.
3. Fetch Artwork Details
Endpoint: GET https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/objects/{objectID}
Retrieves specific details about an artwork using its unique objectID.
Requirements
Node.js: Ensure Node.js is installed on your machine. Download it from nodejs.org.
npm: Used for managing dependencies.
Setup & Usage
1. Clone the repository
Clone this repository to your local machine:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/Hovhannisyan00/Metropolitan-back.git
2. Install dependencies
Navigate to the project directory and install the required dependencies:

bash
Copy code
cd Metropolitan-back
npm install
3. Run the application
Start the application:

bash
Copy code
npm start
4. Testing the API
You can test the search functionality using Postman or curl. For example, to search for "cylinder" in the "Ancient Near Eastern Art" department, use the following request:

bash
Copy code
GET https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/search?q=cylinder
5. Example Use Case
To test the full functionality, you can search for an artwork like "cylinder" within the "Ancient Near Eastern Art" department. The first 10 matching results with their titles will be displayed.

